        <div class="board-card">
            <span class="section-number">01</span>
            <h2>The Global STEM Crisis</h2>
            <p class="mb-3">The challenge is not unique to Kenya. According to <strong>UNESCO</strong>, the world will need <strong>85 million</strong> more tech workers by 2030. However, the infrastructure to teach these skills is missing in the Global South.</p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-2">
                <div class="stat-box">
                    <div class="stat-val text-red-400">2.5M</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">Engineer Shortage (Africa)</div>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-box">
                    <div class="stat-val text-orange-400">80%</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">Schools lack Labs</div>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-box">
                    <div class="stat-val text-yellow-400">$300</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">Avg. Kit Cost (Global)</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 02. LOCAL CONTEXT (CBC) -->
        <div class="board-card">
            <span class="section-number">02</span>
            <h2>The Local Challenge: CBC Implementation</h2>
            <p>Kenya's <strong>Competency-Based Curriculum (CBC)</strong> mandates Coding and Robotics for Junior Secondary. While the policy is visionary, the reality on the ground is stark:</p>
            <ul class="mt-2 space-y-2">
                <li class="flex items-center gap-2 bg-slate-800/50 p-2 rounded">
                    <span class="text-red-500 font-bold">✖</span>
                    <span><strong>The Hardware Wall:</strong> A class of 40 students requires ~KES 140,000 for basic kits. Most public schools operate on shoestring budgets.</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-center gap-2 bg-slate-800/50 p-2 rounded">
                    <span class="text-red-500 font-bold">✖</span>
                    <span><strong>The Fear Factor:</strong> Teachers and students fear damaging expensive components, stifling curiosity and experimentation.</span>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ========================================== -->
    <!-- PAGE 2: OBJECTIVES & HYPOTHESIS -->
    <!-- ========================================== -->
    <div class="print-page">
        <!-- 03. OBJECTIVES -->
        <div class="board-card">
            <span class="section-number">03</span>
            <h2>Project Objectives</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                <div class="border border-slate-700 p-3 rounded">
                    <h3 class="text-sky-400">1. Accessibility</h3>
                    <p class="text-xs">To lower the cost of an IoT lab from KES 5,000 per student to <strong>KES 0</strong>.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="border border-slate-700 p-3 rounded">
                    <h3 class="text-green-400">2. Safety</h3>
                    <p class="text-xs">To create a sandbox where students can make mistakes (short circuits) without consequences.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="border border-slate-700 p-3 rounded">
                    <h3 class="text-purple-400">3. Guidance</h3>
                    <p class="text-xs">To provide a 1:1 AI Tutor that explains <em>concepts</em>, scaling quality instruction.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="border border-slate-700 p-3 rounded">
                    <h3 class="text-yellow-400">4. Authenticity</h3>
                    <p class="text-xs">To ensure the virtual experience builds skills transferable to physical hardware.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 04. HYPOTHESIS -->
        <div class="board-card bg-slate-900 border-l-4 border-l-purple-500">
            <span class="section-number">04</span>
            <h2>Hypothesis</h2>
            <p class="text-lg italic text-slate-200 font-light leading-relaxed">
                "If we can simulate the physical behavior of microcontrollers within a browser environment and augment it with context-aware Artificial Intelligence, then we can enable students in resource-constrained settings to achieve mastery in Embedded Systems without physical hardware."
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- 05. THE INNOVATION -->
        <div class="board-card">
            <span class="section-number">05</span>
            <h2>The Innovation: "FUNDI"</h2>
            <p class="mb-3">FUNDI (Swahili for 'Expert/Technician') is not just a simulator; it is a comprehensive <strong>Virtual Learning Environment (VLE)</strong>.</p>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between text-xs text-center">
                <div class="w-1/4">
                    <div class="bg-blue-500 h-2 w-full mb-1 rounded"></div>
                    Interactivity
                </div>
                <div class="w-1/4">
                    <div class="bg-green-500 h-2 w-full mb-1 rounded"></div>
                    Realism
                </div>
                <div class="w-1/4">
                    <div class="bg-purple-500 h-2 w-full mb-1 rounded"></div>
                    Intelligence
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

